                                              Slot
                                            -----------

  Slot: - It is nothing but a passing a markup from Parent to child.
      Details: - Two Types of Slot.
                                    a). Unnamed slot (Default slot).
                                    b). Named Slot

        UnNamed and Named slot both are in once code pls look on the below.

  Parent Comp
------------------

        import { LightningElement } from 'lwc';
        export default class P_Slot_Parent extends LightningElement {}

<template>
    <lightning-card title="Slot Parent">
        <c-p_-slot_child> <!-- To pass the markup from parent to child need to use the kebab with child compnent name-->
            <p style="color:red">Hello from UnNamed or default Slot</p> <!-- UnNamed Slot but in child side need to use slot tag to get the value. -->
            <p slot='body' style="color:blue">Hello from Named Slot</p> <!-- Named Slot from parent side need to set the slot attribute and get in child side by using slot tag with name attibute -->
        </c-p_-slot_child>
    </lightning-card>
</template>


    child Comp
------------------------

import { LightningElement } from 'lwc';
export default class P_Slot_child extends LightningElement {}

<template>
    <lightning-card title="Slot child">
            <h1> Hello from child</h1>
            <slot></slot> <!-- Recieved Unamed slot, it is mandatory to use to recieve the markup in child side.-->
            <slot name="body"></slot> <!-- Named slot by using name attibut getting markup from parent side.-->
    </lightning-card>
</template>

